{"id":41153,"date":"2023-09-08T19:25:53","date_gmt":"2023-09-08T15:25:53","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=41153"},"modified":"2023-09-08T19:25:53","modified_gmt":"2023-09-08T15:25:53","slug":"makkah-quds-masjid-aqsa","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2023\/09\/08\/makkah-quds-masjid-aqsa\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Masajid: Mecca, Jerusalem, then earth"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Abu Dharr reported: I asked the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, about the first mosque placed on the earth. The Prophet said, \u201c<strong>It was the Sacred Mosque.<\/strong>\u201d I asked, \u201cThen which one?\u201d The Prophet said, \u201c<strong>The furthest mosque in Jerusalem.<\/strong>\u201d I said, \u201cHow long was between them?\u201d The Prophet said, \u201c<strong>Forty years, then the earth was made a mosque for you. Wherever the time for prayer reaches you, then pray there.<\/strong>\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 3366, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 520<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <strong><em>Muttafaqun Alayhi<\/em><\/strong> (authenticity agreed upon) according to Al-Bukhari and Muslim<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u200c\u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a \u0630\u064e\u0631\u064d\u0651 \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0633\u064e\u0623\u064e\u0644\u0652\u062a\u064f \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0645\u064e \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0648\u0651\u064e\u0644\u0650 \u0645\u064e\u0633\u0652\u062c\u0650\u062f\u064d \u0648\u064f\u0636\u0650\u0639\u064e \u0641\u0650\u064a \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0623\u064e\u0631\u0652\u0636\u0650 \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0